7319 /* pre-scale lfe fir coefficients
7320  *
7321  * Permuted compared to table D.8 in the spec. First, the table in the
7322  * spec has twice the number of coefficients, but they are reflected,
7323  * T[i] = T[511 - i]. Furthermore, the indices are permuted, so that
7324  *
7325  * lfe_fir_64[8 * k + j] = T[64 * j + k]
7326  *
7327  * for 0 <= k < 32 and 0 <= j < 8. (This corresponds to adding a
7328  * leading zero to the 8-bit index, and rotating it right by 3 bits
7329  * as a 9-bit field). Values with j >= 4 can be reflected, as
7330  *
7331  * lfe_fir_64[8 * k + j] = T[64 * (7 - j) + (63 - k)]
7332  *
7333  * so all values in T get included. */
7334 #define SCALE(c) ((c) / (256.0f * 32768.0f))
7335 DECLARE_ALIGNED(16, const float, ff_dca_lfe_fir_64)[256] = {
7336  SCALE(2.658434386830777e-4), SCALE(9.029330685734748e-3),
7337  SCALE(7.939263433218002e-2), SCALE(2.425158768892288e-1),
7338  SCALE(3.430179357528686e-1), SCALE(2.398228943347931e-1),
7339  SCALE(7.746443897485733e-2), SCALE(8.622321300208569e-3),
7340  SCALE(8.179365249816328e-5), SCALE(9.450953453779220e-3),
7341  SCALE(8.134882897138596e-2), SCALE(2.451938837766648e-1),
7342  SCALE(3.429597318172455e-1), SCALE(2.371159791946411e-1),
7343  SCALE(7.556436210870743e-2), SCALE(8.229630999267101e-3),
7344  SCALE(9.439323912374676e-5), SCALE(9.887560270726680e-3),
7345  SCALE(8.333285897970200e-2), SCALE(2.478559017181396e-1),

7466 /* Permuted compared to table D.8 in the spec. First, the table in the
7467  * spec has twice the number of coefficients, but they are reflected,
7468  * T[i] = T[511 - i]. Furthermore, the indices are permuted, so that
7469  *
7470  * lfe_fir_128[4 * k + j] = T[128 * j + k]

7472  * for 0 <= k < 64 and 0 <= j < 4. Values with j >= 2 can be

7474  *
7475  * lfe_fir_128[4 * k + j] = T[128 * (3 - j) + (127 - k)]
